The paper discusses techniques for efficient model calibration in Big Data applications, which involves processing and analyzing large datasets. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DB (database) sub-category. The paper also mentions support vector machines and logistic regression models, which are commonly used in machine learning, indicating that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (machine learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses parallel processing and optimization, which are relevant to the cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions Bayesian processes and online aggregation, which are techniques used in artificial intelligence, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-category.
